com.milk.util
Interface Comparator

All Known Implementing Classes:
EqComparator, EqualsComparator
public interface Comparator

This interface is for objects which know how to compare objects for equality and generate relevant hashcodes to make that determination quicker.

Author:
Dan Bornstein, danfuzz@milk.com

compareHash

public int compareHash(java.lang.Object obj)
Get the compare-hash for the given object. If two objects have the same compare-hash from a given Comparator then it's possible for them to be considered equal via compare (). If two objects have different compare-hashes, then they are definitely not equal in terms of compare ().

Parameters:
obj - the object to figure the hash of
Returns:
the compare-hash of the object
